<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Soften" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Soften,</orth> 1) tr. to make soft: <bibl n="shak. luc 591" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 591</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 2, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 4, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 1, 21</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to become soft or tender: <cit><quote>how he may s. at the sight o' the child,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 2, 40</bibl></cit>.
